snippet.textDisplay:
mate I drive an LN167 with all terrain tyres, alloy bull bar, 40ch UHF and an awning. inside I stack my stuff in the tray in tubs, rated recovery points and carry first aid kits, fire extinguisher along with basic recovery gear; snatch strap, equalizer strap, shackles, max trax, air compressor and a hand winch. Yet to find anywhere I can't go.

Bog standard suspension, bog standard (well maintained) engine that's done 360,000kms and runs like brand new ... For the most part people just need to learn to drive their car not mod it.

Gotta admit I love seeing people cruising around with brand new high lift jacks mounted to their roof racks with no jacking points on the car :)

snippet.textDisplay:
14:50 "You can't tune an engine to be more efficient"
Late mail Ronny, yes you can. A good tune will provide more Hp, more Nm and better fuel efficiency - I have that tune in my TT V10 Touareg. 355Hp at all wheels and 960Nm of tractive effort. Eight liters/100 Km on a highway run; 22 in Sand, in Low, with the centre diff locker on.
Oh, btw, I run 255/55/19s; been down to 16psi on sand and rocks - it's all about the wheel strength.

snippet.textDisplay: This is why my tourer turned out to be a disco3.  offroad height at demand, 17"inch rims, modestly oversized rubber, the speedo indicates correct to the point pretty much, the tires i use are Cooper Discoverer AT3 4s (I face a lot of snowy conditions and those are 3PMSF rated) if it becomes icy or deep snow and mud i may put chains on to stay safe and improve traction, so they also have to fit. The car is stable and just works, clocked 306000km's now. I only use it for trips, so maintenance is low price but top quality, I do everything my self and that pushes the price point down significantly, i always upgrade parts with improved parts, enhanced suspension bushes for instance. I absolutely LOVE that car!! If it was viable id have an 80 series LC, but at that price point where i live i could probably get 3 disco 3's. So no land cruiser for me, i rather drive a 100% maintained LR D3.
